<div type="definition">
<p>COMMAND an ARMY to ACT:engage in WARFARE.</p>
    </div>
<div type="notes">
<div type="old-chinese-criteria">
<p>1. The current general word for deploying troops is chén 陳 which connotes arrangement of things in ordered formations, and the more general yòng 用.</p>
<p>2. Zhāng 張 emphasises the spreading out of the troops.</p>
<p>3. Cuò 錯 / 措 emphasises the putting in place of the troops.</p>
        </div>
